Program: Discovery
Title: The discovery of Hydrogen-3+
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwsc
Last Broadcast Date: 10 December 1996
The discovery of Hydrogen-3+. Scientists have been aware of its existence and have finally found proof it exists in deep cold space. Also in the programme, the life and work of Mary Leakey, the anthropologist who discovered the oldest fossil of an extinct ape related to humans.